prompt:
Add a public function called SumList to Collections.calr that creates a list of integers, dynamically adds some values with §PUSH, and returns the sum. The function takes no parameters and returns i32.

Use this exact Calor list syntax:
§F{f001:SumList:pub}
  §O{i32}
  §LIST{lst:i32}
  §/LIST{lst}
  §PUSH{lst} 10
  §PUSH{lst} 20
  §PUSH{lst} 30
  §B{sum} 0
  §EACH{e001:item} lst
    §ASSIGN sum (+ sum item)
  §/EACH{e001}
  §R sum
§/F{f001}

The collection syntax:
- §LIST{id:type} §/LIST{id} creates an empty List<type>
- §PUSH{id} value adds a value to the list dynamically
- §EACH{id:var} collection iterates over items
